race.comment: WINEACLOCKSUMWHERE (6) bolted in here two back before holding his own in the Regional Final at Ascot last time out, beaten just 2L. Back to his preferred track and trip today and he has the speed to offset the tricky draw. Racing in top order, he gets in here light and he looks set to return to winning ways. FLYING SOUTH (7) got a long way back first-up but flew home to just miss over this track and trip. Fitter for that effort and he boasts a solid second-up record. Drawn well again this time around and if he can sit closer in the run, he'll be hard to fend off. THE SPRUIKER (4) is better than we saw last start at Ascot when getting well back and never featuring. Back to this trip is some query, but he's back onto his home deck today and improvement is on the cards. MEAN FEAT (9) has trialled nicely coming in and is not to be discounted.
